{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> δέρρις</b>, εως, ἡ, <br /> (<i>Attic dialect</i> form of Δέρσις, compare δέρω) <b>skin,</b> δ. τριχίνη [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Zech.13.4, compare “Anthologia Graeca” 12.33 (1st c.BC: Meleager Epigrammaticus). \">LXX+1st c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>leathern covering,</b> of a jerkin, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Eupolis Comicus 328 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of a curtain, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Comicus 240, 5th c.BC: Myrtilus Comicus 1. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> in <i>plural</i> (<i>singular</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd-2nd c.BC: Philo Mechanicus “(Belopoeica) Excerpte aus Philons Mechanik - Ath. Berl. Akad.” 95.34)\">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>], <b>screens of skin</b> or <b>hide,</b> hung before fortifications to deaden the enemy's missiles, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.75, 1st c.BC: Cicero, M. Tullius Orator et Philosophus “Epistulae ad Atticum” 4.19.1, 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 20.9, 2nd c.AD: Apollodorus Damascenus Mechanicus “Abhandlungen der Göttinger Gesellschaft der Wissenschaften (Phil.-hist. Klasse)” 142.2, 2nd c.AD: Polyaenus Historicus 3.11.13 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: generally, <b>curtain,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Exo.26.7, +others, “IG” 5(1).1390.35 (Andania, 1st c.BC). \">LXX+1st c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G6801","accentedUnicode":"δέρρις","shortDef":"a hide covering","mediumDef":"a hide covering","stepGloss":"a hide covering","stepTransliteration":"derris","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}